FBIS4-56016 "dreeu101_d_94012" FBIS-EEU-94-101 Daily Report 23 May 1994 SLOVAKIA Radiation Monitoring To Be Linked to Austria Radiation Monitoring To Be Linked to Austria LD2305121594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1000 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305121594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1000 GMT 23 May 94 Slovak BFN [Summary] A Slovak-Austrian agreement under which equipment for the exchange of data from the two countries' radiation early warning systems is to be linked in September this year was signed in Bratislava today. At present Austria has 336 radio measuring stations and Slovakia has 26. Under the agreement, data will be exchanged free of charge and provided to other authorities in both countries as well.
